CARES Act Provides Free Internet for Eligible Families

The State Legislature has designated a portion of the federal CARES Act funding to be used to supply at least 100,000 households with free internet through December 2020.

To be eligible, the household must meet all of the following:
-Have at least one PreK-12th grade student in the household attending Ware Shoals School District 51;
-Household does not currently have internet service;
-Need internet for educational purposes in response to the COVID-19 pandemic;
-Meet income requirements provided on our website.

More information and a required survey can be found on our website. The survey must be completed by August 5, 2020.

